Sarabun Thin Regular (Sarabun-Thin.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin' = NID 1 'Sarabun Thin'.

Sarabun Thin Italic (Sarabun-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-ThinItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Sarabun Thin Italic (Sarabun-ThinItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Thin Italic' = NID 1 'Sarabun Thin' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Sarabun ExtraLight Regular (Sarabun-ExtraLight.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight' = NID 1 'Sarabun ExtraLight'.

Sarabun ExtraLight Italic (Sarabun-ExtraLightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraLight Italic' = NID 1 'Sarabun ExtraLight' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-Light', Everything looks good.

Sarabun Light Italic (Sarabun-LightItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Light Italic' = NID 1 'Sarabun Light' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-Medium', Everything looks good.

Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-Medium', Everything looks good.

Pass

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium' = NID 1 'Sarabun Medium'.

Sarabun Medium Italic (Sarabun-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-MediumItalic', Everything looks good.

Pass

Sarabun Medium Italic (Sarabun-MediumItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'Medium Italic' = NID 1 'Sarabun Medium' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Sarabun SemiBold Regular (Sarabun-SemiBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold' = NID 1 'Sarabun SemiBold'.

This font software is the property of Monotype Imaging Inc., or one of its affiliated entities (collectively, Monotype) and its use by you is covered under the terms of a license agreement. You have obtained this font software either directly from Monotype or together with software distributed by one of the licensees of Monotype. This software is a valuable asset of Monotype. Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. You may not copy or distribute this software. If you have any questions concerning your rights you should review the license agreement you received with the software. You can learn more about Monotype by clicking here: www.monotype.com.

Sarabun SemiBold Italic (Sarabun-SemiBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'SemiBold Italic' = NID 1 'Sarabun SemiBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

Sarabun Bold (Sarabun-Bold.ttf)

name

Mac NID 6

Mac NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-Bold', Everything looks good.

Pass

Sarabun Bold (Sarabun-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-Bold', Everything looks good.

Sarabun ExtraBold Regular (Sarabun-ExtraBold.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold' = NID 1 'Sarabun ExtraBold'.

Pass

Mac NID 6

NID 6 is 'Sarabun-ExtraBoldItalic', Everything looks good.

Unless you have entered into a specific license agreement granting you additional rights, your use of this software is limited by the terms of the actual license agreement you have entered into with Monotype. Sarabun ExtraBold Italic (Sarabun-ExtraBoldItalic.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

NID 16 'Sarabun' + 'Space' + NID 17 'ExtraBold Italic' = NID 1 'Sarabun ExtraBold' + 'Space' + NID 2 'Italic'.

Pass

The result of sTypoAscender – sTypoDescender (1300) match or exceed the unitsPerEm value (1000).
